		<category><![CDATA[jabber]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://stpeter.im/?p=2233</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[As posted on the jingle@xmpp.org discussion list, I&#8217;ve just published new versions of the three core specifications for negotiating multimedia sessions over XMPP: XEP-0166 (the Jingle core), XEP-0167 (the RTP sessions application type), and XEP-0176 (the ICE-UDP transport method). These modifications incorporate our consensus from the XMPP Summit last week and bring us a few [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As <a href='http://mail.jabber.org/pipermail/jingle/2008-July/000143.html'>posted</a> on the <a href='http://mail.jabber.org/mailman/listinfo/jingle'>jingle@xmpp.org</a> discussion list, I&#8217;ve just published new versions of the three core specifications for negotiating multimedia sessions over XMPP: <a href='http://www.xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0166.html'>XEP-0166</a> (the Jingle core), <a href='http://www.xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0167.html'>XEP-0167</a> (the RTP sessions application type), and <a href='http://www.xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0176.html'>XEP-0176</a> (the ICE-UDP transport method). These modifications incorporate our consensus from the <a href='http://www.xmpp.org/summit/summit5.shtml'>XMPP Summit</a> last week and bring us a few steps closer to finalization of the Jingle technologies. Enjoy!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
