		<item>
		<title>Exchanging Cell ID Data Over XMPP</title>
		<link>https://stpeter.im/?p=2231</link>
		<comments>https://stpeter.im/?p=2231#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Jul 2008 04:30:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>stpeter</dc:creator>
		
		<category><![CDATA[jabber]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://stpeter.im/?p=2231</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[My Jabber friend kael poked me today about the possibility of exchanging mobile network Cell IDs over XMPP (probably via personal eventing). This is desirable because, as the Google Gears project explains it, &#8220;many devices do not have native access to GPS or other location data&#8221; and &#8220;GPS can take a long time to get [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>My Jabber friend kael poked me today about the possibility of exchanging mobile network Cell IDs over XMPP (probably via <a href='http://www.xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0163.html'>personal eventing</a>). This is desirable because, as the Google Gears project <a href='http://code.google.com/p/gears/wiki/GeolocationAPI#Network_Location_Provider_Protocol'>explains it</a>, &#8220;many devices do not have native access to GPS or other location data&#8221; and &#8220;GPS can take a long time to get an accurate location fix, drains battery, and does not work indoors.&#8221; So that means we either need to add Cell IDs to <a href='http://www.xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0080.html'>XEP-0080</a> or define a separate XMPP extension (I vote for the latter). The parameters seem pretty straightforward (check out the XML format at <a href='http://celldb.org/aboutapi.php'>celldb.org</a>) and Cell ID payloads could be used by all sorts of mobile XMPP clients and applications such as <a href='http://blog.buddycloud.com/node/1'>Buddycloud</a>, <a href='http://www.nokia.com/betalabs/chat'>Nokia Chat</a>, <a href='http://bombus-im.org/'>Bombus</a>, <a href='http://lampiro.bluendo.com/'>Lampiro</a>, and many more.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re interested in discussing this idea, join the <a href='http://mail.jabber.org/mailman/listinfo/mobile'>mobile@xmpp.org</a> email list.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
