		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://stpeter.im/?p=2228</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I got an email from rabble overnight asking for some quick notes about our consensus on OAuth + XMPP from yesterday&#8217;s discussion at the XMPP Summit, so here goes&#8230;
Scenario: I want my Twhirl client to receive Kellan&#8217;s tune stream from last.fm via XMPP.


My Twhirl client asks last.fm for an OAuth token.


If last.fm considers me a [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I got an email from <a href='http://anarchogeek.com/'>rabble</a> overnight asking for some quick notes about our consensus on OAuth + XMPP from yesterday&#8217;s discussion at the <a href='http://www.xmpp.org/summit/summit5.shtml'>XMPP Summit</a>, so here goes&#8230;</p>
<p>Scenario: I want my <a href='http://www.twhirl.org/'>Twhirl</a> client to receive <a href='http://www.last.fm/music/Kellan+Elliott-McCrea'>Kellan&#8217;s tune stream</a> from <a href='http://last.fm/'>last.fm</a> via XMPP.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>My Twhirl client asks last.fm for an OAuth token.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If last.fm considers me a friend of Kellan&#8217;s, it grants a token.</p>
</li>
<li>My Twhirl client sends an XMPP pubsub subscription request to last.fm, with appropriate OAuth bits:</p>
<pre>
&lt;iq type='set'
    from='random-id@twhirl.org'
    to='last.fm'
    id='sub1'&gt;
  &lt;pubsub xmlns='http://jabber.org/protocol/pubsub'&gt;
    &lt;subscribe jid='random-id@twhirl.org'
               node='/music/Kellan+Elliott-McCrea'/&gt;
    &lt;oauth xmlns='urn:xmpp:oauth'&gt;
      &lt;oauth_consumer_key>0685bd9184jfhq22&lt;/oauth_consumer_key&gt;
      &lt;oauth_token>ad180jjd733klru7&lt;/oauth_token>
      &lt;oauth_signature_method&gt;PLAINTEXT+HMAC-SHA1&gt;/oauth_signature_method&gt;
      &lt;oauth_signature&gt;wOJIO9A2W5mFwDgiDvZbTSMK%2FPY%3D&lt;/oauth_signature>
    &lt;/oauth&gt;
  &lt;/pubsub&gt;
&lt;/iq&gt;
</pre>
<p>Where oath_signature is:</p>
<p>sign(consumer key,consumer secret,token,token secret)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If the token and signature are verified, access is granted.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Whee, I receive real-time last.fm updates in my Twhirl client!</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>I&#8217;ll be updating <a href='http://www.xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0235.html'>XEP-0235</a> along these lines later today, but I might not get those revisions done before rabble&#8217;s talk at 11:30. :)</p>
]]></content:encoded>
